The paper deals with image inpainting using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new deep generative model-based approach, which involves training a shared network twice with different targets, indicating the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of contextual information and high-level semantics, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the optimization of feature maps, which is a common topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
